<item>
            <title>[LU-19934] Adapt asynchronous API in compressors</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19934</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In kernel 6.17, the zstd and deflate compressors are using acomp API in their implementation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;zstd commit: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/f5ad93ffb54119a8dc5e18f070624d4ead586969&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/f5ad93ffb54119a8dc5e18f070624d4ead586969&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;deflate commit: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/08cabc7d3c8638b078e0ac2f755cead1defafe91&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/08cabc7d3c8638b078e0ac2f755cead1defafe91&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can adapt this on our compressors implementation along with some cleanup and improvements.&lt;br/&gt;
In addition we can get rid of `libcfs/include/libcfs/compr_private/scompress.h` and use the one exposed by the kernel `/include/crypto/internal/scompress.h` which will make things simpler in future changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/08cabc7d3c8638b078e0ac2f755cead1defafe91&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/08cabc7d3c8638b078e0ac2f755cead1defafe91&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
